1
00:00:01,010 --> 00:00:04,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Emma Greene in the 624
crosses the finish line!</i></font>

2
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:06,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}She puts herself in provisional third!</i></font>

3
00:00:06,770 --> 00:00:09,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Her time was nip and tuck
with the pair at the top!</i></font>

4
00:00:09,990 --> 00:00:15,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}After day six of qualifying, four drivers
have beaten last year's course record!</i></font>

5
00:01:44,130 --> 00:01:46,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><font face="Impact"><font size="90"><b><font color="#d1082a">MF Ghost</font></b></font></font></font>

6
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:46,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><b><font face="Arial"><font color="#ff060f">m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100</font></font></b></font>

7
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:50,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><b><font face="Arial">The King's
Impatience</font></b></font>

8
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Oh, the camera's on me.</i></font>

9
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:53,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yay! Make sure I look cute, okay?</font>

10
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:56,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Marie, this is dangerous now.</i></font>

11
00:01:57,180 --> 00:02:01,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Your costume's so tight, we're a breath away
 from a wardrobe malfunction.</i></font>

12
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Out on the course, the final day
 of qualifying is underway.</i></font>

13
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:09,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Wading through the Hydro Trap
 is the 6 car,</i></font>

14
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:13,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}driven by the original cornering wizard,
 Yanagida Takuya.</i></font>

15
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:17,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He negotiates the high-speed S-curve
 beside Benten Rock.</i></font>

16
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:21,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And while he looked unsteady earlier 
in the season, he's in better shape lately.</i></font>

17
00:02:22,330 --> 00:02:26,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}This powerful front-engine RWD BMW
 is like an extension of his limbs.</i></font>

18
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:30,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}It's his belief that the only way 
to turn properly is with rear-wheel drive.</i></font>

19
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:33,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And he's dead set on 
confirming his conviction!</i></font>

20
00:02:34,170 --> 00:02:36,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Yes, it's our solitary 
rear-wheel drive specialist,</i></font>

21
00:02:36,930 --> 00:02:41,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}who's always near the top of 
the popularity charts: Yanagida Takuya.</i></font>

22
00:02:41,050 --> 00:02:44,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You need more than complete control 
over a car to call yourself a pro driver.</i></font>

23
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:48,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You're not a racing driver 
until you post times that show it.</i></font>

24
00:02:51,490 --> 00:02:54,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>The final day of qualifying
should be underway in Atami.</i></font>

25
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:58,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'm certain Mr. Beckenbauer 
will set an impressive time,</i></font>

26
00:02:58,930 --> 00:03:00,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>but my real concern is...</i></font>

27
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:02,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Mr. Moroboshi.</i></font>

28
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:13,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The 885 shoots away!</i></font>

29
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:16,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He qualified eighth 
on his debut at Peninsula,</i></font>

30
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:18,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}but managed to climb
 to fifth in the race.</i></font>

31
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:24,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Overshadowed by Katagiri Kanata, 
who made 10 overtakes in one race,</i></font>

32
00:03:24,730 --> 00:03:26,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}his drive didn't get much attention...</i></font>

33
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:33,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}...but no one can deny that finishing fifth
 on debut is deserving of high praise.</i></font>

34
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:37,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As the graduates of England's RDRS
steal the spotlight...</font>

35
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:40,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}...here we have a domestic thoroughbred, 
born and raised in Gunma.</i></font>

36
00:03:41,310 --> 00:03:43,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Let's keep an eye on him.</i></font>

37
00:03:43,380 --> 00:03:48,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Beckenbauer. Katagiri Kanata.
 And Sawatari Koki.</i></font>

38
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:50,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>The three of you are damn fast.</i></font>

39
00:03:51,420 --> 00:03:54,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>But compared to how my boss drives
when he's serious on public roads?</i></font>

40
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:59,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You three are no big deal. 
I know he's got you beat.</i></font>

41
00:03:59,050 --> 00:04:03,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>When I think about it in those terms, 
I feel a lot more relaxed.</i></font>

42
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:07,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>The Godly Fifteen's big three
 are nothing to sweat over.</i></font>

43
00:04:07,470 --> 00:04:10,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And I'm gonna make it a big four.</i></font>

44
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:15,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And he's through the Hydro Trap! 
The 885 gains an attention flag!</i></font>

45
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:18,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I've been wondering this
 for a while, but...</font>

46
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:22,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Isn't MFG's flag system 
a little, well, funky, boss?</font>

47
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:26,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're only noticing that now? 
What took you so long?</font>

48
00:04:27,780 --> 00:04:33,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The algorithm might assign the flags,
 but the actual judgment?</font>

49
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:36,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's based on one man's theory 
about maximum speed street racing.</font>

50
00:04:37,770 --> 00:04:39,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The man who built MFG.</font>

51
00:04:40,150 --> 00:04:40,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So basically,</font>

52
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:45,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the system rewards people who drive 
in a way my brother would approve of.</font>

53
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:47,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Makes sense.</font>

54
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:51,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I guess that's why Fujiwara's student
is always getting attention flags.</font>

55
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:55,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The blonde girl from yesterday 
proved that pretty clearly.</font>

56
00:04:55,810 --> 00:04:58,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And Sena's starting to reflect that, too.</font>

57
00:04:58,290 --> 00:05:00,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did something happen 
between you and Sena, boss?</font>

58
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:02,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nothing major.</font>

59
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:06,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I just gave him a big dose of something
 that'll keep him stable.</font>

60
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:10,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I have no idea what that means, 
but it seems to have done the trick.</i></font>

61
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Have we ever had a hotter crop 
of rookies than this year's batch?</i></font>

62
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:21,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The 86 on day five! The 624 on day six!</i></font>

63
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:24,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And today, we have the 885!</i></font>

64
00:05:24,910 --> 00:05:28,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}These big-numbered cars are thriving!</i></font>

65
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:32,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}How far will these supernovas 
burning with potential go?</i></font>

66
00:05:32,210 --> 00:05:34,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Sena roars onward!</i></font>

67
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:43,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}In this end-of-summer, high-speed battle,</i></font>

68
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:47,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}we've almost reached the climax of 
qualifying for Seaside Double Lane.</i></font>

69
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:50,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And here to wrap it up is this man,</i></font>

70
00:05:50,370 --> 00:05:54,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}his golden number 12 shining
on an all-new white chassis.</i></font>

71
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:58,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The overwhelming favorite 
to win it all this season.</i></font>

72
00:05:58,380 --> 00:06:01,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Reigning undefeated
on a three-win streak.</i></font>

73
00:06:01,590 --> 00:06:04,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}A driver strong enough 
to see off all challengers.</i></font>

74
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:08,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Yes, the absolute king, 
Michael Beckenbauer, has arrived.</i></font>

75
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:13,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That German hottie is
undressing me with his eyes.</i></font>

76
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:15,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>It's embarrassing, but fantastic.</i></font>

77
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:18,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Five, four, three, two, one!</i></font>

78
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:24,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And he's off! The invincible 
Porsche is on its way!</i></font>

79
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:25,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><font face="Verdana"><font size="22"><font color="#3a444a">Ogata Automotive Ltd.</font></font></font></font>

80
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:27,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That's a Cayman GT4.</i></font>

81
00:06:28,010 --> 00:06:32,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>It's only the fourth race, but 
we're already facing a "last boss" car.</i></font>

82
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:36,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The vehicle selected by 
the absolute king for this race</i></font>

83
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:40,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}is, surprisingly, a three-pedal manual 
transmission with an H-pattern shifter!</i></font>

84
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:43,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That's just like ours!</i></font>

85
00:06:56,350 --> 00:06:59,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sorry, Wakana. I was hoping 
to get some advice.</font>

86
00:06:59,730 --> 00:07:02,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't mind. I wasn't doing 
anything this Sunday, anyway.</font>

87
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:06,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, after what you said, I went home
 and rewatched the third race,</font>

88
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:11,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and the guest analyst said Kanata 
was only participating for one year.</font>

89
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:13,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, so Yuka was right?</font>

90
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:15,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's a real shock.</font>

91
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:18,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It hasn't come up at home?</font>

92
00:07:18,290 --> 00:07:22,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">My parents took in Kanata assuming
 he wouldn't be leaving for a while.</font>

93
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:27,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So unless he brings it up, 
I doubt they'd even think to ask.</font>

94
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:33,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Which means Kanata-san's 
the only one who knows for sure.</font>

95
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You'll have to find the guts to ask him.</font>

96
00:07:39,090 --> 00:07:41,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I could never. I'm too scared.</font>

97
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:44,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't want to think 
about life without Kanata.</font>

98
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:49,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Something inside me just wants 
to preemptively reject the truth.</font>

99
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:53,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't want to know.
I don't even wanna <i>think</i> about it.</font>

100
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:57,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I've never seen you so worked up
 over something, Ren.</font>

101
00:07:57,580 --> 00:08:02,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's not confirmed he's leaving yet, 
so don't let it get you down.</font>

102
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:07,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What would you do, Wakana?</font>

103
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:10,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'd find the courage to ask him,
 even if I was afraid.</font>

104
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:13,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If he's gonna leave one way or another,</font>

105
00:08:13,710 --> 00:08:17,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the sooner I accept that and make
 the most of the time that's left,</font>

106
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the fewer regrets I'd have.</font>

107
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:22,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're so strong, Wakana.</font>

108
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:26,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, going through seven boyfriends
 teaches you a thing or two.</font>

109
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:30,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Wait, seven? She added another 
while I wasn't looking.</i></font>

110
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:34,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I really loved some of them.</font>

111
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:37,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Just thinking about it makes me 
wanna cry to this day.</font>

112
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:43,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You really oughta tell him how you feel,
 Ren, or I know you'll regret it.</font>

113
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:49,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He zooms into Sector 2!</i></font>

114
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:53,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He's managing to keep pace 
with the 4 and 86.</i></font>

115
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:00,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}What a thrilling run.</i></font>

116
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:03,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}This is the usual fare 
from the absolute king.</i></font>

117
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:05,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}His driving may not </i>look<i> aggressive,</i></font>

118
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}but one glance at his time
has your jaw dropping.</i></font>

119
00:09:08,570 --> 00:09:11,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He usually matches his rivals' pace
 over the first half,</i></font>

120
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:15,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}then kicks it up a notch
 and blasts his way to the finish!</i></font>

121
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:23,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}No writer could concoct a narrative 
so full of catharsis as this man's driving.</i></font>

122
00:09:24,450 --> 00:09:27,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Booth to Michael. Things are going 
according to your plan so far.</font>

123
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:31,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You went through the checkpoint 
within two-tenths of the 4's time. Over.</font>

124
00:09:32,050 --> 00:09:36,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>This is easy. Sawatari and Katagiri 
are both unremarkable.</i></font>

125
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:39,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Or is it because the GT4 
is simply on another level?</i></font>

126
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:48,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He enters Sector 3! 
And I feel this is where...</font>

127
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:50,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}...we'll see something spectacular.</i></font>

128
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:54,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The absolute king's absolute sprint 
is about to be unleashed!</i></font>

129
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He's on the attack!</i></font>

130
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:07,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The 12's clearly moving
 differently now!</i></font>

131
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:10,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Booth to Michael.
Time to kick it up a gear.</i></font>

132
00:10:10,570 --> 00:10:13,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You're currently 0.3 seconds
behind the 4 car. Over.</i></font>

133
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:16,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>What? That can't be right.</i></font>

134
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:18,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Wait a minute. Crap.</i></font>

135
00:10:19,430 --> 00:10:22,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Sawatari, you bastard. 
I walked right into your trap.</i></font>

136
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I should've expected your trickery.</i></font>

137
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:30,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm going radio silent now. 
Keep me updated on our times. Over.</font>

138
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:35,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>There's still time. 
This is where it really begins.</i></font>

139
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He's now in the middle of Sector 3,</i></font>

140
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:41,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}and he's lagging behind 
the 4 by 0.28 seconds.</i></font>

141
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:43,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Will he be able to turn this around?</i></font>

142
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:46,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}This is odd. This isn't what 
we've come to expect from him.</i></font>

143
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:50,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Is the absolute king
struggling here on Double Lane?</i></font>

144
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:55,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Beckenbauer seems to be panicking.</i></font>

145
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>It was the same for Kanata.</i></font>

146
00:10:57,580 --> 00:11:01,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Towards the end of Sector 3, 
he started losing time to the 4 car.</i></font>

147
00:11:02,110 --> 00:11:05,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That means Sawatari Koki 
was going uniquely fast.</i></font>

148
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:08,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>But how did he manage it?</i></font>

149
00:11:19,780 --> 00:11:22,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That braking error is going to cost me.</i></font>

150
00:11:23,150 --> 00:11:25,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I've lost this head-to-head.</i></font>

151
00:11:26,010 --> 00:11:27,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Now you've done it, Sawatari.</i></font>

152
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:31,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You have my thanks for helping me 
find motivation for this race.</i></font>

153
00:11:32,370 --> 00:11:36,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And I intend to pay you back
 with interest.</i></font>

154
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He approaches the final corner.</i></font>

155
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:42,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And he's 0.13 seconds behind 
without enough road left to catch up!</i></font>

156
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:48,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The king, Beckenbauer, finishes his lap
0.02 seconds off the top spot!</i></font>

157
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:50,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And so, it is Sawatari
 in the 4 car</i></font>

158
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:54,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}who grabs a second 
career pole, the first 
of this season.</i></font>

159
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:56,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}We also see 
that six drivers</i></font>

160
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:59,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}have beaten last season's
 course record.</i></font>

161
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:03,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Better, but still a way to go.</i></font>

162
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:14,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'm really scared about 
telling Kanata I love him.</i></font>

163
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:19,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Once I do, it could mean 
the end of everything.</i></font>

164
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:24,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>If I am going to tell him, 
it's going to be at the very end.</i></font>

165
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:29,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>But if Kanata's gonna go far away...</i></font>

166
00:12:29,580 --> 00:12:32,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>If I'm never gonna see him again...</i></font>

167
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:36,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Will there be any point 
in telling him how I feel?</i></font>

168
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:40,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I have no idea what to do.</i></font>

169
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:44,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I guess I really am a lonely only child 
who knows nothing about romance.</i></font>

170
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:49,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I feel sick. Grandma, help.</i></font>

171
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:00,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}MF Ghost.</i></font>

172
00:13:02,060 --> 00:13:06,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I have to say, that was the most 
exciting qualifying I've ever seen.</font>

173
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:08,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Everyone's leveled up so much.</font>

174
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:12,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I mean, six drivers managed 
to beat last year's course record.</font>

175
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:15,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sawatari Koki, in particular,
 was absolutely on it.</font>

176
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:19,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Speaking of that, how do you think
 he managed it, Okuyama-san?</font>

177
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:21,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He gambled on a long shot.</font>

178
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:27,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The three sections of Double Lane each 
place different demands on suspension.</font>

179
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The toll roads of Sector 1</font>

180
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:33,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">are smooth enough that suspension 
set up for circuit racing will work well.</font>

181
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:36,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But Sector 3 is the exact opposite.</font>

182
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:40,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The roads are a patch job, 
sending cars bouncing all over the place.</font>

183
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:45,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Now, standard procedure would be 
to optimize the suspension for Sector 2,</font>

184
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:47,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">which is sort of halfway between,</font>

185
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:52,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but I'm guessing the 4 was set up
 for Sector 3's bumpy roads.</font>

186
00:13:53,060 --> 00:13:55,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why would he do that?</font>

187
00:13:55,370 --> 00:14:00,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Beckenbauer tends to pace himself
based on laps set by his rivals.</font>

188
00:14:00,090 --> 00:14:02,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The plan was to use that against him.</font>

189
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:07,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He probably thought it was a breeze
as he entered Sector 3.</font>

190
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:12,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The fact he didn't notice
Sawatari's trap earlier</font>

191
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:16,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">may have been carelessness from the 
absolute king. Or maybe overconfidence?</font>

192
00:14:17,180 --> 00:14:21,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">By comparison, Sawatari tackling 
Sector 1 with a flexible suspension</font>

193
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:23,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">set up for Sector 3 
probably deserves praise.</font>

194
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:28,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He'll likely go with a more standard 
setup for the actual race, but...</font>

195
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:31,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Damn, Sawatari.</i></font>

196
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:33,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>He's a real tactician. Talk about shrewd.</i></font>

197
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:40,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's said that out of all five courses,
 Double Lane is the hardest on tires.</font>

198
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:44,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It'll be tough for Sawatari 
to stay ahead even starting on pole.</font>

199
00:14:44,670 --> 00:14:49,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I imagine Beckenbauer will be raging
 after his pride took a knock.</font>

200
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:53,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And our <i>own</i> driver clearly 
left a lot in the tank, too.</font>

201
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:56,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Tomorrow's race is gonna be a wild one.</font>

202
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:10,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Please, God. Don't take 
Kanata away from me.</i></font>

203
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:16,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I've always thought it strange we haven't
 found the backdrop to this picture.</font>

204
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:20,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We've found some similar buildings, 
but we could never get the right angle.</font>

205
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:23,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't give up. I <i>know</i> we can find it.</font>

206
00:15:23,820 --> 00:15:28,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'll never stop looking. 
I'm gonna keep searching until I find it.</font>

207
00:15:29,370 --> 00:15:31,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">When you're trying so hard,</font>

208
00:15:31,850 --> 00:15:35,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can hardly give up the search, 
since I'm the one who started it.</font>

209
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Right. It's a promise, then.</font>

210
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:44,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>This might be my last hope.</i></font>

211
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:56,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So, honey, do you have a girlfriend?</font>

212
00:15:56,910 --> 00:16:01,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know some girls. 
But I'm bad at talking to them.</font>

213
00:16:01,970 --> 00:16:04,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why do you ask, Mum?</font>

214
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:07,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Can you recall the faces 
of those friends clearly?</font>

215
00:16:07,790 --> 00:16:12,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Of course! You and I are good
 at that. Right, Mum?</font>

216
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's true.</font>

217
00:16:13,570 --> 00:16:17,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But there will come a time 
when you're older and in love</font>

218
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:22,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">where you'll try to recall someone's face
 and struggle to do so.</font>

219
00:16:22,730 --> 00:16:24,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">When people are in love,</font>

220
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:28,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><font color="#ffffff">something in the brain stops them from 
accurately recalling their love's face.</font></font>

221
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why does the brain do that?</font>

222
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:33,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, you get anxious when 
you forget something, right?</font>

223
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:37,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The anxiety makes you want
 to see them again.</font>

224
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:42,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You want to be able to look 
at your love whenever you want.</font>

225
00:16:42,420 --> 00:16:45,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's how the brain works 
when you're in love.</font>

226
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:48,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did that happen to you, Mum?</font>

227
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:49,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Of course it did.</font>

228
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:52,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">When I was in love with your father,
 that's how it was.</font>

229
00:16:53,180 --> 00:16:56,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What about me? 
Can you remember my face?</font>

230
00:16:56,690 --> 00:16:58,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Now <i>that</i> I can do.</font>

231
00:16:58,290 --> 00:17:03,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Do you realize how many portraits
 of you I have in my studio?</font>

232
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:07,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't like that.</font>

233
00:17:08,090 --> 00:17:13,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't be silly. You're the one I care
 the most about in the world.</font>

234
00:17:13,170 --> 00:17:15,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No one else comes close.</font>

235
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:18,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But that's a different feeling
 than romantic love.</font>

236
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:20,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You understand, don't you, my boy?</font>

237
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:28,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>What Mum told me was true.</i></font>

238
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:32,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I never took a picture like this
 before coming to Japan.</i></font>

239
00:17:33,690 --> 00:17:37,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Being unable to recall
a certain girl's face clearly...</i></font>

240
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:41,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That's never happened to me before.</i></font>

241
00:17:42,580 --> 00:17:44,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'm in love with Ren.</i></font>

242
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:51,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'm not sure when it started, 
but I'm realizing now that it's true.</i></font>

243
00:17:52,650 --> 00:17:56,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I should be happy, 
but I feel so unbelievably tense.</i></font>

244
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:59,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>After all, I have to leave
 Japan eventually.</i></font>

245
00:18:00,410 --> 00:18:05,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'm not sure what to do. 
And I have no one I can talk to about it.</i></font>

246
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:08,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I wonder what kind of advice
 Mum would give me.</i></font>

247
00:18:09,910 --> 00:18:12,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>What would Dad say if he were here?</i></font>

248
00:18:15,660 --> 00:18:18,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I miss them both so much.</i></font>

249
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:27,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Welcome to all 37.2 million
 MFG fans out there.</i></font>

250
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:29,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}I'm your commentator, Tanaka Yoji.</i></font>

251
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:31,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The end of summer heralds
 a high-speed battle.</i></font>

252
00:18:31,930 --> 00:18:35,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The Seaside Double Lane race
 is about to begin.</i></font>

253
00:18:35,530 --> 00:18:39,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Today's guest in the booth
is Sudo Kyoichi-san.</i></font>

254
00:18:39,890 --> 00:18:44,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Sudo-san's had a long career as 
one of All-Japan Rally's top competitors...</i></font>

255
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:48,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">...and is a trustee on 
the MFG steering committee.</font>

256
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:51,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sudo-san, thanks for joining us.</font>

257
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:53,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's a pleasure to be here.</font>

258
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:57,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I come from the world of rally, 
meaning I won't have much to share</font>

259
00:18:57,420 --> 00:19:00,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">regarding overtaking tactics
 and techniques,</font>

260
00:19:00,380 --> 00:19:02,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">so I might not be the best of fits.</font>

261
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:06,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But when it comes to driving 
at high speeds on public roads,</font>

262
00:19:06,690 --> 00:19:08,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know a thing or two.</font>

263
00:19:09,230 --> 00:19:12,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}So I'll do what I can 
to share that knowledge.</i></font>

264
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:14,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}I hope to enlighten and entertain.</i></font>

265
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:21,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ren. You're Ren, aren't you?</font>

266
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Emma-san?</font>

267
00:19:22,580 --> 00:19:25,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I thought I'd seen you somewhere before.</font>

268
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:32,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I watched the third race in London and saw
 you give Kanata his congratulatory kiss.</font>

269
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:37,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I remember thinking, "That girl's got 
a nice figure," so you left an impression.</font>

270
00:19:37,550 --> 00:19:38,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I had no idea.</font>

271
00:19:39,540 --> 00:19:43,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Huh? Emma Greene's talking to Ren-chan?</i></font>

272
00:19:44,130 --> 00:19:46,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I had no idea her English was so good.</i></font>

273
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:49,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I have a request for you, Ren.</font>

274
00:19:50,670 --> 00:19:54,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If you care about Kanata...
If you care about his future...</font>

275
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:58,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't try to keep him in Japan.</font>

276
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:03,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Racing drivers with talent like his
 are incredibly rare.</font>

277
00:20:04,180 --> 00:20:08,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But the longer he stays here, 
the more opportunities he'll miss out on.</font>

278
00:20:08,610 --> 00:20:11,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And I can't just stand by
 and let that happen.</font>

279
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:15,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So I'm begging you, Ren. <font face="Times New Roman">Please.</font></font>

280
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:22,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That's not fair, Emma-san.</i></font>

281
00:20:22,570 --> 00:20:25,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That's really, really unfair.</i></font>

282
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:31,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Something wrong, Ren-chan? You look 
like you're about to burst into tears.</font>

283
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:34,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kyoko-san.</font>

284
00:20:35,490 --> 00:20:39,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Being a woman is about being able
 to smile even when it hurts.</font>

285
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:42,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And our job as Angels is to smile.</font>

286
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:46,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Right. Of course.</font>

287
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:49,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's better. You've got this.</font>

288
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:53,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Now, let's get to work. Step lively.</font>

289
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's almost time for the race to start.</font>

290
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Right.</font>

291
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:58,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Five minutes to the race start.</i></font>

292
00:20:59,190 --> 00:21:03,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The competitors leave the paddock
 and head to the start line.</i></font>

293
00:21:03,770 --> 00:21:07,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Sudo-san, what will you be 
looking out for in today's race?</i></font>

294
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:09,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Good question.</i></font>

295
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:14,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}First, I want to see how the big three
interact in the early stages.</i></font>

296
00:21:14,790 --> 00:21:19,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In terms of total distance, 
Double Lane is the longest of all five races.</font>

297
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:24,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's a major risk of punishing the tires
 early on if the pace is too high.</font>

298
00:21:25,650 --> 00:21:31,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}So with their uncanny sprinting skills,
 how will this trio play it?</i></font>

299
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:36,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And what will the rookies in fourth and fifth
 do as a result of what happens ahead?</i></font>

300
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:39,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Moroboshi Sena and 
Emma Greene, you mean?</i></font>

301
00:21:40,220 --> 00:21:46,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}If they can insert themselves into 
the trio's tussle, it'll be absolute chaos.</i></font>

302
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:48,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}It's an exciting setup, that's for sure.</i></font>

303
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:52,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Is this a polygon of MFG rivalries
in a new Warring States period?</i></font>

304
00:21:53,370 --> 00:21:55,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Ren, give me strength.</i></font>

305
00:21:59,350 --> 00:22:00,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I have three cars ahead of me.</i></font>

306
00:22:01,260 --> 00:22:05,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And Katagiri Kanata's right in front of me.
 I couldn't ask for a better spot.</i></font>

307
00:22:05,730 --> 00:22:08,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I've had a plan in mind for this
since qualifying ended.</i></font>

308
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:12,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Katagiri is my sole target for this race.</i></font>

309
00:22:12,810 --> 00:22:16,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'll cling to him like a plunger
and won't let go, no matter what.</i></font>

310
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:19,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Then, on the final lap, we'll duke it out.</i></font>

311
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:24,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I don't care about the other cars. 
Or the overall positions in the race.</i></font>

312
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>This is a one-on-one 
between me and Katagiri.</i></font>

313
00:22:27,870 --> 00:22:30,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The Angels are all lined up.</i></font>

314
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:35,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Sawatari Koki in pole position is guided
 slowly through the gate by a drone.</i></font>

315
00:22:36,310 --> 00:22:38,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Next comes Beckenbauer in the 12 car.</i></font>

316
00:22:38,950 --> 00:22:41,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Then, it's Katagiri Kanata in the 86.</i></font>

317
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:48,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Moroboshi Sena in the 886. 
Emma Greene in the 624.</i></font>

318
00:22:48,150 --> 00:22:52,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Akaba Kaito in the 2.
 Aiba Shun in the 9.</i></font>

319
00:22:53,290 --> 00:22:55,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Suppressing the urge to speed off,</i></font>

320
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:58,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}these 15 drivers focus 
on the drones in front of them,</i></font>

321
00:22:58,430 --> 00:23:01,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}waiting for that light to turn green.</i></font>

322
00:23:02,090 --> 00:23:06,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And the 16, our final competitor, 
passes through the gate!</i></font>

323
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:08,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And there's the green!</i></font>

324
00:23:10,020 --> 00:23:12,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Listen to that cacophony!</i></font>

325
00:23:14,450 --> 00:23:21,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The waves in Sagami Bay will be sent back
 to the sea by the sheer intensity!</i></font>

326
00:23:32,860 --> 00:23:36,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Next time, Turn 35: The Strongest Train.</i></font>

